The '''Giant Sea Snake''' is encountered at the end of the [[Royal Trouble]] quest. It is not as strong as its combat level suggests, but some form of [[Poison#Curing_poison|antipoison]] is vital, as the snake can inflict poison that starts at 9 damage. It fights with [[melee]] up close and [[ranged]] from a distance, but it cannot detect the use of [[prayer]]s. Like its [[Sea Snake Young|offspring]], it is vulnerable to [[Magic]]. It drops the [[heavy box]] which is needed to finish the quest, and it can only be fought once.

Level 40 [[Slayer]] is required to kill this creature.

The best way to defeat the snake is to attack it from afar with magic to exploit its weakness. Players can freely use [[Protect from Missiles]] to reduce all the damage besides poison. Other factors such as what food to bring and what armour and weapon to use are left to the player to decide. It is recommended to bring at least [[lobster]]s or [[swordfish]]. A [[dwarf multicannon]] can be set up nearby.

